imsprog (1.8.5-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * QA Upload to fix FTBFS and packaging issues.
  * Fix FTBFS on Big Endian architectures (Closes: #1140616):
    - Restrict architecture build to little-endian systems via d/control.
  * Address feedback from lintian and sponsor (Hugh McMaster):
    - Completely rewrite debian/copyright to match DEP-5 specification,
      grouping files correctly by copyright holder.
    - Add missing license definitions for ch34x_i2c and ch341funcs files.
    - Remove invalid entries and fix incorrect authorship claims.
    - Format Upstream-Contact email with angle brackets and drop redundant
      emails from individual file stanzas.
    - Drop obsolete Priority and Rules-Requires-Root fields from d/control.
    - Upgrade debian/watch parser to format version 5.
    - Remove unnecessary debian/NEWS and debian/*.maintscript files.

 -- Mikhail Medvedev <e-ink-reader@yandex.ru>  Wed, 24 Jun 2026 11:55:00 +0300

